.TH "drm_connector_attach_max_bpc_property" 9 "drm_connector_attach_max_bpc_property" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_connector_attach_max_bpc_property \- attach "max bpc" property
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_connector_attach_max_bpc_property
.BI "(struct drm_connector *connector "  ","
.BI "int min "  ","
.BI "int max "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "connector" 12
connector to attach max bpc property on.
.IP "min" 12
The minimum bit depth supported by the connector.
.IP "max" 12
The maximum bit depth supported by the connector.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is used to add support for limiting the bit depth on a connector.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero on success, negative errno on failure.
